.TH SHOREWALL-NFT-NOTRACK 5 "2026-04-24" "shorewall-nft 1.11.0" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
shorewall\-nft\-notrack \- connection tracking bypass rules for shorewall-nft
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.I notrack
file defines flows that should bypass the kernel connection tracking
subsystem.  For each matching packet the compiler emits a
.B notrack
statement in the
.B prerouting raw
chain (nft priority
.BR -300 ).

Bypassing conntrack can significantly improve throughput for high-rate
flows (e.g. inter-router peering, monitoring traffic) at the cost of losing
stateful tracking for those flows.

.SH FILE FORMAT
Location:
.I /etc/shorewall/notrack
(or inside a merged
.IR /etc/shorewall46/ ).
.PP
Columns are whitespace-separated.  Lines beginning with
.B #
are comments.

.TS
l l l.
Column	Required	Description
_
SOURCE	yes	Source zone, zone:address, bare CIDR, or - for any
DEST	yes	Destination zone, zone:address, bare CIDR, or - for any
PROTO	no	Protocol filter
DPORT	no	Destination port filter
SPORT	no	Source port filter
USER	no	User/group match
.TE
.PP
The SOURCE and DEST columns accept three shapes:
.IP \(bu 2
.B zone
\- the zone's interfaces become an
.B iifname
filter on emit; no address predicate
.IP \(bu 2
.B zone:addr
\- both
.B iifname
and
.B "ip [d]addr"
predicates are emitted
.IP \(bu 2
bare
.B addr
or
.B addr/cidr
\- only the
.B "ip [d]addr"
predicate is emitted; no iifname filter (any interface)
.PP
A
.B zone
in the SOURCE column always produces an
.B iifname
match against the zone's bound interfaces, mirroring classic
Shorewall's per-zone
.B <zone>_ctrk
chain dispatched from
.B PREROUTING
via
.BR "-i <iface> -j <zone>_ctrk" .
A bare IP / CIDR in either column lands as the corresponding
.B "ip [s/d]addr"
predicate; without this the
.B notrack
verdict would fire for traffic to / from any address on the
matching protocol+port.

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Bypass tracking for high-rate BGP peering traffic:
.RS
.nf
#SOURCE          DEST             PROTO  DPORT
10.0.0.1         10.0.0.2         tcp    179
.fi
.RE
.PP
Bypass tracking for SNMP polling:
.RS
.nf
10.0.99.5        -                udp    161
.fi
.RE
.PP
Bypass tracking for all traffic on a monitoring interface:
.RS
.nf
mon              all
.fi
.RE
.PP
Bypass tracking for inbound DNS to two named-server hosts (bare-IP
destination, source zone gates the iifname filter on emit):
.RS
.nf
#SOURCE          DEST             PROTO  DPORT
net              10.0.0.53        udp    53
net              10.0.0.54        udp    53
.fi
.RE

.SH NFSET / DNS TOKENS
The SOURCE and DEST columns accept
.BR nfset:<name> ,
.BR dns:<hostname> ,
and
.BR dnsr:<hostname>
tokens — see
.BR shorewall\-nft\-rules (5)
and
.BR shorewall\-nft\-nfsets (5)
for the full grammar.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shorewall\-nft (8),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-conntrack (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-nfsets (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-rules (5)

